                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12704346" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2009 21:15:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yeah, the python docs say that _&lt;em&gt;repr&lt;/em&gt;_ should be used if there is no _&lt;em&gt;str&lt;/em&gt;_ and every other case I have seen follows that rule but the exception printing apparently does not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12704353" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2009 21:38:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;created &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.python.org/issue5882&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.python.org/issue5882&lt;/a&gt;, although that&apos;s only of academic interest for existing versions of python &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12704402" author="tlipcon" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2009 23:24:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that implements _&lt;em&gt;str&lt;/em&gt;_ only for the case of Exception-type structs by calling through to _&lt;em&gt;repr&lt;/em&gt;_&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12704407" author="dreiss" created="Wed, 29 Apr 2009 23:35:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll be interested to see how the Python folks respond.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12704418" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2009 00:13:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;They responded, &quot;Exception implements _&lt;em&gt;str&lt;/em&gt;_ so this is not a bug.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
